{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735973540,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_function_bef8rixhda56_1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/","description":"List lineages folder contents"},"output":"total 0\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 4 michelkerkmeester  staff  128 Jun  6 10:52 .\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 8 michelkerkmeester  staff  256 Jun  6 10:52 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 3 michelkerkmeester  staff   96 Jun  6 10:52 deepseek\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 3 michelkerkmeester  staff   96 Jun  6 10:52 minimax\n","metadata":{"output":"total 0\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 4 michelkerkmeester  staff  128 Jun  6 10:52 .\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 8 michelkerkmeester  staff  256 Jun  6 10:52 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 3 michelkerkmeester  staff   96 Jun  6 10:52 deepseek\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 3 michelkerkmeester  staff   96 Jun  6 10:52 minimax\n","exit":0,"description":"List lineages folder contents","truncated":false},"title":"List lineages folder contents","time":{"start":1780735973537,"end":1780735973539}},"id":"prt_e9c22933e001JWHnkOBvGjvxng","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","messageID":"msg_e9c227882001jcDUC1xWiDsEr0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735974910,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_bef8rixhda56_3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions (parity matrix, daemon-dependency audit, MCP-only affordances, integration-surface migration, architecture comparison with go/no-go).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n2: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek\",\"minimax\",\"mimo\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":5,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\"}\n\n(End of file - total 2 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions (parity matrix, daemon-dependency audit, MCP-only affordances, integration-surface migration, architecture comparison with go/no-go).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek\",\"minimax\",\"mimo\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":5,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\"}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl","text":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions (parity matrix, daemon-dependency audit, MCP-only affordances, integration-surface migration, architecture comparison with go/no-go).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek\",\"minimax\",\"mimo\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":5,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\"}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":2,"totalLines":2,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl","time":{"start":1780735974897,"end":1780735974905}},"id":"prt_e9c229ded001FH4sKxBb48wke4","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","messageID":"msg_e9c227882001jcDUC1xWiDsEr0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735974910,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_bef8rixhda56_2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions: KQ1 parity matrix for all 37 tools with a CLI equivalent per tool (prior art: generate-context.js already does memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs under scripts/dist/memory/); KQ2 daemon-dependency audit (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs — what dies per architecture); KQ3 MCP-only affordances and replacements (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable plus session-proxy replay semantics); KQ4 integration-surface migration (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap and memory_context, agents allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools); KQ5 comparison of a/b/c with effort estimates, risk register, go/no-go recommendation. Evidence: a mid-session MCP disconnect left Claude Code unable to reconnect while a CLI re-bridges per call; the launcher/IPC layer already speaks JSON-RPC over daemon-ipc.sock.\",\n3:   \"maxIterations\": 5,\n4:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0,\n5:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n6:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n7:   \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n8:   \"resource_map_present\": false,\n9:   \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": true },\n10:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\n11:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n12:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n13:   \"lineage\": {\n14:     \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\n15:     \"parentSessionId\": null,\n16:     \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n17:     \"generation\": 1,\n18:     \"continuedFromRun\": null\n19:   },\n20:   \"fanout\": {\n21:     \"executors\": [\n22:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"deepseek\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 },\n23:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"minimax\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5, \"timeoutSeconds\": 1500 },\n24:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"mimo\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 }\n25:     ],\n26:     \"concurrency\": 2\n27:   }\n28: }\n\n(End of file - total 28 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions: KQ1 parity matrix for all 37 tools with a CLI equivalent per tool (prior art: generate-context.js already does memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs under scripts/dist/memory/); KQ2 daemon-dependency audit (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs — what dies per architecture); KQ3 MCP-only affordances and replacements (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable plus session-proxy replay semantics); KQ4 integration-surface migration (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap and memory_context, agents allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools); KQ5 comparison of a/b/c with effort estimates, risk register, go/no-go recommendation. Evidence: a mid-session MCP disconnect left Claude Code unable to reconnect while a CLI re-bridges per call; the launcher/IPC layer already speaks JSON-RPC over daemon-ipc.sock.\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 5,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": true },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"fanout\": {","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions: KQ1 parity matrix for all 37 tools with a CLI equivalent per tool (prior art: generate-context.js already does memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs under scripts/dist/memory/); KQ2 daemon-dependency audit (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs — what dies per architecture); KQ3 MCP-only affordances and replacements (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable plus session-proxy replay semantics); KQ4 integration-surface migration (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap and memory_context, agents allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools); KQ5 comparison of a/b/c with effort estimates, risk register, go/no-go recommendation. Evidence: a mid-session MCP disconnect left Claude Code unable to reconnect while a CLI re-bridges per call; the launcher/IPC layer already speaks JSON-RPC over daemon-ipc.sock.\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 5,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": true },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"fanout\": {\n    \"executors\": [\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"deepseek\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 },\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"minimax\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5, \"timeoutSeconds\": 1500 },\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"mimo\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 }\n    ],\n    \"concurrency\": 2\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":28,"totalLines":28,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json","time":{"start":1780735974889,"end":1780735974908}},"id":"prt_e9c229891001p0McgtHqeUZUyc","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","messageID":"msg_e9c227882001jcDUC1xWiDsEr0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735976274,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_bef8rixhda56_4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy\n2: \n3: ## Topic\n4: \n5: Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar.\n6: \n7: ## Key Questions\n8: \n9: - [ ] KQ1: What is the CLI equivalent for each of the 37 MCP tools (full parity matrix)? Prior art: `generate-context.js` already performs memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs exist under `scripts/dist/memory/`.\n10: - [ ] KQ2: Which features depend on a long-lived daemon (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs), and what dies under each architecture?\n11: - [ ] KQ3: Which affordances exist ONLY because of the MCP protocol (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable + session-proxy replay), and what are the concrete CLI replacements?\n12: - [ ] KQ4: What does migrating every current MCP caller entail (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap/memory_context, agents' allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools)?\n13: - [ ] KQ5: How do architectures a/b/c compare on the zero-feature-loss bar, effort, and risk — and what is the go/no-go recommendation?\n14: \n15: ## Known Context\n16: \n17: Verified facts available at init (from pre-run exploration of this repo; lanes should re-verify citations independently):\n18: - The MCP server registers 37 tools across 5 registry files under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/` (memory 16, context 1, causal 4, checkpoint 4, lifecycle 12).\n19: - The launcher/daemon layer (`.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` + `lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`) already speaks JSON-RPC over a unix socket (`daemon-ipc.sock`); the MCP-protocol-specific surface is the stdio transport + tool schemas + session-proxy replay classification.\n20: - Daemon-resident services: local-first embedding cascade (ollama → hf-local → OpenAI → Voyage) with warm model server, chokidar file-watcher, async embedding retry queue, RSS watchdog with in-place recycle, owner-lease single-writer model.\n21: - CLI prior art: `scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` (canonical save), plus reindex/cleanup/validate/backfill/rank maintenance CLIs.\n22: - Operational evidence FOR de-MCP-ing: 2026-06-06 mid-session MCP disconnect (owner session closed; bridged secondary rode the ~41s reattach ladder, gave up, and Claude Code never reconnects MCP mid-session — 45 tools lost for the session). A per-call CLI would have re-bridged.\n23: - Evidence AGAINST / costs: MCP gives agents automatic tool discovery + schemas + per-tool permission gating; hooks and agents across 4 runtimes currently call MCP tools directly.\n24: \n25: ## Negative Knowledge (ruled out)\n26: \n27: - (none yet)\n28: \n29: ## Next Focus\n30: \n31: Start with KQ1 (parity matrix) and KQ2 (daemon-dependency audit) — they anchor every other question.\n32: \n33: ## Parameters\n34: \n35: - Max iterations: 5 (per lane, terminal cap)\n36: - Convergence threshold: 0 (forced full iteration budget; legal early stop only via all-questions-answered)\n\n(End of file - total 36 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Topic\n\nCan the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [ ] KQ1: What is the CLI equivalent for each of the 37 MCP tools (full parity matrix)? Prior art: `generate-context.js` already performs memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs exist under `scripts/dist/memory/`.\n- [ ] KQ2: Which features depend on a long-lived daemon (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs), and what dies under each architecture?\n- [ ] KQ3: Which affordances exist ONLY because of the MCP protocol (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable + session-proxy replay), and what are the concrete CLI replacements?\n- [ ] KQ4: What does migrating every current MCP caller entail (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap/memory_context, agents' allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools)?\n- [ ] KQ5: How do architectures a/b/c compare on the zero-feature-loss bar, effort, and risk — and what is the go/no-go recommendation?\n\n## Known Context\n\nVerified facts available at init (from pre-run exploration of this repo; lanes should re-verify citations independently):\n- The MCP server registers 37 tools across 5 registry files under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/` (memory 16, context 1, causal 4, checkpoint 4, lifecycle 12).\n- The launcher/daemon layer (`.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` + `lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`) already speaks JSON-RPC over a unix socket (`daemon-ipc.sock`); the MCP-protocol-specific surface is the stdio transport + tool schemas + session-proxy replay classification.\n- Daemon-resident services: local-first embedding cascade (ollama → hf-local → OpenAI → Voyage) with warm model server, chokidar file-watcher, async embedding retry queue, RSS watchdog with in-place recycle, owner-lease single-writer model.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Topic\n\nCan the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [ ] KQ1: What is the CLI equivalent for each of the 37 MCP tools (full parity matrix)? Prior art: `generate-context.js` already performs memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs exist under `scripts/dist/memory/`.\n- [ ] KQ2: Which features depend on a long-lived daemon (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs), and what dies under each architecture?\n- [ ] KQ3: Which affordances exist ONLY because of the MCP protocol (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable + session-proxy replay), and what are the concrete CLI replacements?\n- [ ] KQ4: What does migrating every current MCP caller entail (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap/memory_context, agents' allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools)?\n- [ ] KQ5: How do architectures a/b/c compare on the zero-feature-loss bar, effort, and risk — and what is the go/no-go recommendation?\n\n## Known Context\n\nVerified facts available at init (from pre-run exploration of this repo; lanes should re-verify citations independently):\n- The MCP server registers 37 tools across 5 registry files under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/` (memory 16, context 1, causal 4, checkpoint 4, lifecycle 12).\n- The launcher/daemon layer (`.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` + `lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`) already speaks JSON-RPC over a unix socket (`daemon-ipc.sock`); the MCP-protocol-specific surface is the stdio transport + tool schemas + session-proxy replay classification.\n- Daemon-resident services: local-first embedding cascade (ollama → hf-local → OpenAI → Voyage) with warm model server, chokidar file-watcher, async embedding retry queue, RSS watchdog with in-place recycle, owner-lease single-writer model.\n- CLI prior art: `scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` (canonical save), plus reindex/cleanup/validate/backfill/rank maintenance CLIs.\n- Operational evidence FOR de-MCP-ing: 2026-06-06 mid-session MCP disconnect (owner session closed; bridged secondary rode the ~41s reattach ladder, gave up, and Claude Code never reconnects MCP mid-session — 45 tools lost for the session). A per-call CLI would have re-bridged.\n- Evidence AGAINST / costs: MCP gives agents automatic tool discovery + schemas + per-tool permission gating; hooks and agents across 4 runtimes currently call MCP tools directly.\n\n## Negative Knowledge (ruled out)\n\n- (none yet)\n\n## Next Focus\n\nStart with KQ1 (parity matrix) and KQ2 (daemon-dependency audit) — they anchor every other question.\n\n## Parameters\n\n- Max iterations: 5 (per lane, terminal cap)\n- Convergence threshold: 0 (forced full iteration budget; legal early stop only via all-questions-answered)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":36,"totalLines":36,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1780735976267,"end":1780735976272}},"id":"prt_e9c229df30013j3Il5YBSvAEE7","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","messageID":"msg_e9c227882001jcDUC1xWiDsEr0"}}
