{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780735984916,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_function_ynarscsd6zmk_2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Implementation Plan: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility [system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan]\"\n3: description: \"Single-execution research plan: one /deep:start-research-loop:auto fan-out invocation with three CLI lanes (DeepSeek-v4-pro, MiniMax-M3, MiMo-V2.5-Pro), 5 forced iterations each, concurrency 2.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"mcp cli feasibility plan\"\n6:   - \"fan-out research plan\"\n7:   - \"three lane research\"\n8: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n9: contextType: \"general\"\n10: _memory:\n11:   continuity:\n12:     packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"\n13:     last_updated_at: \"2026-06-06T12:30:00Z\"\n14:     last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n15:     recent_action: \"Authored the research run plan\"\n16:     next_safe_action: \"Launch the 3-lane deep-research fan-out loop\"\n17:     blockers: []\n18:     key_files:\n19:       - \"plan.md\"\n20:     completion_pct: 0\n21:     open_questions: []\n22:     answered_questions: []\n23: ---\n24: # Implementation Plan: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility\n25: \n26: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 1 -->\n27: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: plan-core | v2.2 -->\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: <!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n32: ## 1. SUMMARY\n33: \n34: ### Technical Context\n35: \n36: | Aspect | Value |\n37: |--------|-------|\n38: | **Language/Stack** | deep-loop-runtime (Node CJS) orchestrating cli-opencode lanes |\n39: | **Framework** | `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` fan-out (one lineage per model) |\n40: | **Storage** | File-based JSONL state + registries under `research/` |\n41: | **Testing** | `validate.sh --strict` + `orchestration-summary.json` lane outcomes |\n42: \n43: ### Overview\n44: One fan-out invocation runs three heterogeneous research lanes against the same topic, each with a forced 5-iteration terminal cap, then merges findings and compiles the verdict report. There are no implementation phases: this packet ships research, not code.\n45: <!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: <!-- ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n50: ## 2. QUALITY GATES\n51: \n52: ### Definition of Ready\n53: - [x] Problem statement clear and scope documented\n54: - [x] Success criteria measurable (verdict-shaped report, parity coverage, lane state)\n55: - [x] Dependencies identified (opencode CLI, three provider pools)\n56: \n57: ### Definition of Done\n58: - [ ] All acceptance criteria met (REQ-001..REQ-003 in spec.md)\n59: - [ ] Lane outcomes verified via orchestration summary + per-lane state\n60: - [ ] Docs updated (spec/tasks/implementation-summary) and final strict validation passes\n61: <!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: <!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n66: ## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n67: \n68: ### Pattern\n69: Command-owned research loop with fan-out lineages (no application architecture changes).\n70: \n71: ### Key Components\n72: - **Orchestrator**: `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` resolves setup, spawns lanes, merges, compiles.\n73: - **Lane pool**: `fanout-run.cjs` capped pool (concurrency 2), one opencode subprocess per lane; DeepSeek lane gets `--pure` natively; reasoning effort maps to `--variant high`.\n74: - **Lanes**: deepseek (`deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro`), minimax (`minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`, 1500s per-iteration ceiling), mimo (`xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`).\n75: - **Merge + compile**: `fanout-merge.cjs` dedups findings by id with lineage attribution; reducer compiles `research.md`.\n76: \n77: ### Data Flow\n78: Topic -> per-lane lineage configs (`research/lineages/{label}/`) -> 5 read-only investigation iterations per lane -> per-lane findings registries -> merged registry + attribution -> compiled `research/research.md` + generated spec-findings fence in spec.md.\n79: <!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: <!-- ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->\n84: ## FIX ADDENDUM: AFFECTED SURFACES\n85: \n86: Not applicable: this packet is research-only (`research_intent=feasibility`), no bug fix, no code mutation. Lanes are read-only investigators; the only writes are workflow-owned artifacts under `research/` plus the bounded generated block in spec.md.\n87: \n88: | Surface | Current Role | Action | Verification |\n89: |---------|--------------|--------|--------------|\n90: | research/** | workflow artifact tree | create (workflow-owned) | orchestration-summary.json + validate.sh |\n91: | mk-spec-memory runtime | research subject | unchanged (read-only evidence source) | git status clean outside the packet |\n92: <!-- /ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: <!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n97: ## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n98: \n99: ### Phase 1: Setup\n100: - [x] Packet folder + four core docs authored from v2.2 templates\n101: - [x] description.json + graph-metadata.json generated\n102: - [x] Pre-run `validate.sh --strict` passes (2026-06-06, 0 errors 0 warnings)\n103: \n104: ### Phase 2: Core Execution\n105: - [ ] Launch the fan-out invocation (exact command in tasks.md T003 / approved plan file)\n106: - [ ] Monitor `research/orchestration-status.log` + per-lane iteration files to completion\n107: \n108: ### Phase 3: Verification\n109: - [ ] Merged registry + fanout-attribution.md present; research.md verdict-shaped\n110: - [ ] Per-lane iteration counts recorded; early-stopped lanes documented\n111: - [ ] Reconciliation: tasks ticked, metadata regenerated, final strict validation, continuity saved via generate-context.js\n112: <!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: <!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n117: ## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n118: \n119: | Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n120: |-----------|-------|-------|\n121: | Structural | Packet docs + anchors | validate.sh --strict |\n122: | Lane health | 3 lanes, exit codes 0/2/3, salvage sweeps | orchestration-status.log, orchestration-summary.json |\n123: | Content | Verdict shape: parity matrix, loss table, go/no-go | Manual review against REQ-002/REQ-003 |\n124: <!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: <!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n129: ## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n130: \n131: | Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n132: |------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n133: | opencode CLI 1.16.2 | External | Green | No lanes can run |\n134: | deepseek-api / minimax-token-plan / xiaomi-token-plan pools | External | Green (smoke-tested 2026-06-06) | Affected lane fails; partial merge path applies |\n135: | deep-loop-runtime fan-out scripts | Internal | Green | Fall back to three sequential single-executor loops |\n136: <!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: <!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->\n141: ## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n142: \n143: - **Trigger**: Run produces unusable output or must be abandoned mid-flight.\n144: - **Procedure**: Research-only rollback: stop lanes (pool SIGTERM honors salvage), delete or archive `research/` outputs, revert packet docs via git. No production system is touched.\n145: <!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Implementation Plan: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility [system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan]\"\ndescription: \"Single-execution research plan: one /deep:start-research-loop:auto fan-out invocation with three CLI lanes (DeepSeek-v4-pro, MiniMax-M3, MiMo-V2.5-Pro), 5 forced iterations each, concurrency 2.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"mcp cli feasibility plan\"\n  - \"fan-out research plan\"\n  - \"three lane research\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"general\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-06T12:30:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Authored the research run plan\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Launch the 3-lane deep-research fan-out loop\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files:\n      - \"plan.md\"\n    completion_pct: 0","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Implementation Plan: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility [system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan]\"\ndescription: \"Single-execution research plan: one /deep:start-research-loop:auto fan-out invocation with three CLI lanes (DeepSeek-v4-pro, MiniMax-M3, MiMo-V2.5-Pro), 5 forced iterations each, concurrency 2.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"mcp cli feasibility plan\"\n  - \"fan-out research plan\"\n  - \"three lane research\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"general\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-06-06T12:30:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-opus-4-8\"\n    recent_action: \"Authored the research run plan\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Launch the 3-lane deep-research fan-out loop\"\n    blockers: []\n    key_files:\n      - \"plan.md\"\n    completion_pct: 0\n    open_questions: []\n    answered_questions: []\n---\n# Implementation Plan: Memory MCP to CLI Feasibility\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 1 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: plan-core | v2.2 -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n## 1. SUMMARY\n\n### Technical Context\n\n| Aspect | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| **Language/Stack** | deep-loop-runtime (Node CJS) orchestrating cli-opencode lanes |\n| **Framework** | `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` fan-out (one lineage per model) |\n| **Storage** | File-based JSONL state + registries under `research/` |\n| **Testing** | `validate.sh --strict` + `orchestration-summary.json` lane outcomes |\n\n### Overview\nOne fan-out invocation runs three heterogeneous research lanes against the same topic, each with a forced 5-iteration terminal cap, then merges findings and compiles the verdict report. There are no implementation phases: this packet ships research, not code.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n## 2. QUALITY GATES\n\n### Definition of Ready\n- [x] Problem statement clear and scope documented\n- [x] Success criteria measurable (verdict-shaped report, parity coverage, lane state)\n- [x] Dependencies identified (opencode CLI, three provider pools)\n\n### Definition of Done\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria met (REQ-001..REQ-003 in spec.md)\n- [ ] Lane outcomes verified via orchestration summary + per-lane state\n- [ ] Docs updated (spec/tasks/implementation-summary) and final strict validation passes\n<!-- /ANCHOR:quality-gates -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Pattern\nCommand-owned research loop with fan-out lineages (no application architecture changes).\n\n### Key Components\n- **Orchestrator**: `/deep:start-research-loop:auto` resolves setup, spawns lanes, merges, compiles.\n- **Lane pool**: `fanout-run.cjs` capped pool (concurrency 2), one opencode subprocess per lane; DeepSeek lane gets `--pure` natively; reasoning effort maps to `--variant high`.\n- **Lanes**: deepseek (`deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro`), minimax (`minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3`, 1500s per-iteration ceiling), mimo (`xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro`).\n- **Merge + compile**: `fanout-merge.cjs` dedups findings by id with lineage attribution; reducer compiles `research.md`.\n\n### Data Flow\nTopic -> per-lane lineage configs (`research/lineages/{label}/`) -> 5 read-only investigation iterations per lane -> per-lane findings registries -> merged registry + attribution -> compiled `research/research.md` + generated spec-findings fence in spec.md.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->\n## FIX ADDENDUM: AFFECTED SURFACES\n\nNot applicable: this packet is research-only (`research_intent=feasibility`), no bug fix, no code mutation. Lanes are read-only investigators; the only writes are workflow-owned artifacts under `research/` plus the bounded generated block in spec.md.\n\n| Surface | Current Role | Action | Verification |\n|---------|--------------|--------|--------------|\n| research/** | workflow artifact tree | create (workflow-owned) | orchestration-summary.json + validate.sh |\n| mk-spec-memory runtime | research subject | unchanged (read-only evidence source) | git status clean outside the packet |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n\n### Phase 1: Setup\n- [x] Packet folder + four core docs authored from v2.2 templates\n- [x] description.json + graph-metadata.json generated\n- [x] Pre-run `validate.sh --strict` passes (2026-06-06, 0 errors 0 warnings)\n\n### Phase 2: Core Execution\n- [ ] Launch the fan-out invocation (exact command in tasks.md T003 / approved plan file)\n- [ ] Monitor `research/orchestration-status.log` + per-lane iteration files to completion\n\n### Phase 3: Verification\n- [ ] Merged registry + fanout-attribution.md present; research.md verdict-shaped\n- [ ] Per-lane iteration counts recorded; early-stopped lanes documented\n- [ ] Reconciliation: tasks ticked, metadata regenerated, final strict validation, continuity saved via generate-context.js\n<!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n\n| Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n|-----------|-------|-------|\n| Structural | Packet docs + anchors | validate.sh --strict |\n| Lane health | 3 lanes, exit codes 0/2/3, salvage sweeps | orchestration-status.log, orchestration-summary.json |\n| Content | Verdict shape: parity matrix, loss table, go/no-go | Manual review against REQ-002/REQ-003 |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n|------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n| opencode CLI 1.16.2 | External | Green | No lanes can run |\n| deepseek-api / minimax-token-plan / xiaomi-token-plan pools | External | Green (smoke-tested 2026-06-06) | Affected lane fails; partial merge path applies |\n| deep-loop-runtime fan-out scripts | Internal | Green | Fall back to three sequential single-executor loops |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->\n## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n\n- **Trigger**: Run produces unusable output or must be abandoned mid-flight.\n- **Procedure**: Research-only rollback: stop lanes (pool SIGTERM honors salvage), delete or archive `research/` outputs, revert packet docs via git. No production system is touched.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":145,"totalLines":145,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/plan.md","time":{"start":1780735984905,"end":1780735984913}},"id":"prt_e9c22c504001RI9YoCH8qtDP3J","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","messageID":"msg_e9c22aa68001J2LH5uKR16Ec60"}}
