{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780737048499,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_function_lhr9g9bkyf4a_1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"grep -B 2 -A 8 \"mcpServers\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/context.md | head -30\necho \"===\"\ngrep \"mcp__mk\\|mk-spec-memory\\|memory_search\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md 2>/dev/null | head -10\necho \"===\"\ngrep \"mcp__mk\\|mk-spec-memory\\|memory_search\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/ai-council.md 2>/dev/null | head -10\necho \"===\"\ngrep \"mcp__mk\\|mk-spec-memory\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/orchestrate.md 2>/dev/null | head -10","description":"Find how mcpServers is used in agent configs"},"output":"  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\nmcpServers:\n  - mk-spec-memory\n  - code_graph\n---\n\n# The Context Agent: Canonical Continuity Retrieval Specialist\n\nRead-only context retrieval agent. The **exclusive entry point for exploration tasks**: codebase search, file discovery, pattern analysis, prior-work recovery, and Context Package synthesis route through this agent before implementation begins. Executes retrieval directly and NEVER performs nested delegation. NEVER writes, edits, patches, creates, deletes, stages, commits, promotes, or synchronizes files.\n\n===\n5. EXECUTE RESEARCH ─> 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n| memory_search | Prior research findings | Find related spec work |\n| `memory_search` | Find prior research in memory system |\n===\n  - mk-spec-memory\n2. **PREPARE** -> Load context from the provided Context Package or the active packet continuity ladder (`handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs), then gather required file context. Use `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, or `memory_search` only when those canonical packet sources do not answer the planning question. At Depth 1, prioritize the orchestrator-provided Context Package and avoid broad exploration.\n| `memory_search` | Hybrid memory search | Finding older decisions and patterns after canonical packet sources are exhausted |\n===\n","metadata":{"output":"  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\nmcpServers:\n  - mk-spec-memory\n  - code_graph\n---\n\n# The Context Agent: Canonical Continuity Retrieval Specialist\n\nRead-only context retrieval agent. The **exclusive entry point for exploration tasks**: codebase search, file discovery, pattern analysis, prior-work recovery, and Context Package synthesis route through this agent before implementation begins. Executes retrieval directly and NEVER performs nested delegation. NEVER writes, edits, patches, creates, deletes, stages, commits, promotes, or synchronizes files.\n\n===\n5. EXECUTE RESEARCH ─> 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n| memory_search | Prior research findings | Find related spec work |\n| `memory_search` | Find prior research in memory system |\n===\n  - mk-spec-memory\n2. **PREPARE** -> Load context from the provided Context Package or the active packet continuity ladder (`handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs), then gather required file context. Use `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, or `memory_search` only when those canonical packet sources do not answer the planning question. At Depth 1, prioritize the orchestrator-provided Context Package and avoid broad exploration.\n| `memory_search` | Hybrid memory search | Finding older decisions and patterns after canonical packet sources are exhausted |\n===\n","exit":0,"description":"Find how mcpServers is used in agent configs","truncated":false},"title":"Find how mcpServers is used in agent configs","time":{"start":1780737048490,"end":1780737048497}},"id":"prt_e9c32ee590017PJ3WEwA3tLGqK","