 then run session_bootstrap() or memory_context() in resume mode with profile=resume and only ask for extra memory when the recovery packet is still missing something important\\\"\\n\\n  Line 90:     tool: memory_context\\n\\n  Line 100:     - \\\"If next safe action is missing, use session_bootstrap() or memory_context(mode: resume, profile: resume) then targeted memory_search on next-steps/state\\\"\\n\\n  Line 164:       - Attempt session_bootstrap() or memory_context() with mode=\\\"resume\\\" and profile=\\\"resume\\\" for the resolved spec folder\\n\\n  Line 168:     context_priority: [\\\"handover.md\\\", \\\"_memory.continuity\\\", \\\"supporting spec docs\\\", \\\"session_bootstrap()\\\", \\\"memory_context(mode: resume, profile: resume)\\\", \\\"memory_search() with resume anchors\\\"]\\n\\n  Line 183:       - If the user chose Fill missing next step / blockers, run targeted anchored memory_search() only for those gaps\\n\\n  Line 184:       - If the user chose Deep context, use `session_bootstrap()`/`memory_context()` plus targeted `memory_search()` to enrich the canonical packet\\n\\n  Line 190:       name: memory_context\\n\\n  Line 191:       note: \\\"Call directly - NEVER through Code Mode. Use it only after the canonical packet is still thin; use anchored memory_search() only when more detail is still needed.\\\"\\n\\n  Line 193:     outputs: { memory_loaded: true, context_source: \\\"handover|continuity|spec_docs|memory_context|memory_search|combined\\\", context_summary: extracted_context, resume_packet: \\\"now|last|next|blockers|artifact\\\" }\\n\\n  Line 259:   memory_search_failed: { action: \\\"Report that supplemental anchored recovery failed\\\", fallback: \\\"Offer to continue with the current /speckit:resume context or start fresh\\\" }\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_confirm.yaml:\\n  Line 126:     tool: memory_search\\n\\n  Line 585:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 594:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 603:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 612:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml:\\n  Line 126:     tool: memory_search\\n\\n  Line 536:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 545:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 554:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 563:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_auto.yaml:\\n  Line 71:   order: [\\\"Primary: handover.md (<24h old)\\\", \\\"Primary: _memory.continuity in implementation-summary.md\\\", \\\"Primary: supporting spec docs (tasks/checklist/plan/decision-record/resource-map)\\\", \\\"Secondary: graph-metadata.json packet hints\\\", \\\"Secondary: session_bootstrap() or memory_context(mode: resume, profile: resume)\\\", \\\"Secondary: memory_search() with resume anchors\\\"]\\n\\n  Line 81:   behavior: \\\"Auto-load handover.md (<24h) first, else run session_bootstrap() or memory_context() in resume mode with profile=resume without prompting; stop as soon as one safe next action can be named\\\"\\n\\n  Line 85:     tool: memory_context\\n\\n  Line 95:     - \\\"If next safe action is missing, read `_memory.continuity`, then use memory_context(mode: resume) and targeted memory_search on next-steps/state\\\"\\n\\n  Line 140:       - If the canonical packet is still insufficient, call session_bootstrap() first or memory_context() with mode=\\\"resume\\\" and profile=\\\"resume\\\"\\n\\n  Line 142:       - If specific essentials are still missing, run targeted anchored memory_search() for those gaps instead of broad loading\\n\\n  Line 144:     context_priority: [\\\"handover.md\\\", \\\"_memory.continuity\\\", \\\"supporting spec docs\\\", \\\"session_bootstrap()\\\", \\\"memory_context(mode: resume, profile: resume)\\\", \\\"memory_search() with resume anchors\\\"]\\n\\n  Line 146:       name: memory_context\\n\\n  Line 147:       note: \\\"Call directly - NEVER through Code Mode. Use it only after the canonical packet is still thin; use anchored memory_search() only for targeted gap filling.\\\"\\n\\n  Line 149:     outputs: { memory_loaded: true, context_source: \\\"handover|continuity|spec_docs|memory_context|memory_search\\\", context_summary: extracted_context, resume_packet: \\\"now|last|next|blockers|artifact\\\" }\\n\\n  Line 194:   memory_search_failed: { action: \\\"Proceed only with essentials already recovered\\\", fallback: \\\"Offer /speckit:resume <spec-folder> or start fresh\\\" }\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_confirm.yaml:\\n  Line 309:     tool: memory_search\\n\\n  Line 330:       note: \\\"Use Code Graph structural queries (code_graph_query) + Grep to verify plan references against codebase patterns; verify hits with Read. memory_search is for spec docs/memory, not arbitrary code.\\\"\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_confirm.yaml:\\n  Line 370:       - { id: memory_context, points: 20 }\\n\\n  Line 476:     tool: memory_search\\n\\n  Line 729:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 738:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 747:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 756:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_auto.yaml:\\n  Line 332:     tool: memory_search\\n\\n  Line 348:       note: \\\"Use Code Graph structural queries (code_graph_query) + Grep to verify plan references against codebase patterns; verify hits with Read. memory_search is for spec docs/memory, not arbitrary code.\\\"\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_auto.yaml:\\n  Line 352:       - { id: memory_context, points: 20 }\\n\\n  Line 449:     tool: memory_search\\n\\n  Line 685:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 694:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 703:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n  Line 712:             Verify hits with Read; do not use memory_search for arbitrary code.\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ask-ai-council_confirm.yaml:\\n  Line 34:     tool: memory_context\\n\\n\\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 101 matches (1 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)\",\"metadata\":{\"matches\":101,\"truncated\":true},\"title\":\"mk-spec-memory|memory_search|memory_context|session_bootstrap\",\"time\":{\"start\":1780736069449,\"end\":1780736069530}},\"id\":\"prt_e9c240bd2001B7B2yDb9k9SYnq\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e9c23f575001FfzCeEuAPaasjU\"}}\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/logs/fanout-lineage.out:{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780736285958,\"sessionID\":\"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"call_00_zFltkXBawAcxLVmhmGX90333\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"content\":\"# Iteration 004: KQ4 — Integration-Surface Migration Map\\n\\n## Focus\\nMap every integration point that currently calls MCP tools and define the migration path to CLI.\\n\\n## Assessment: newInfoRatio=1.0\\n\\nFourth iteration — orthogonal to KQ1-KQ3. This is the \\\"how much work\\\" question.\\n\\n## Findings\\n\\n### Integration Surface Inventory\\n\\n#### Surface 1: Runtime Agent alled-tools\\n\\nEvery agent in `.opencode/agents/` lists mk-spec-memory tools in its allowed-tools or uses them in its instructions.\\n\\n**Evidence from codebase:**\\n\\n| Agent | File | MCP Tools Used | Migration Impact |\\n|-------|------|---------------|-----------------|\\n| **context** | `.opencode/agents/context.md:21,76,96,129,148,162,171,191,195` [SOURCE: file:.opencode/agents/context.md:21] | `memory_context`, `memory_search`, `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_list`, `memory_stats` | Replace MCP tool calls with `spec-memory context/search/match-triggers/list/stats` CLI calls. ~5 references per agent file. |\\n| **deep-research** | `.opencode/agents/deep-research.md:327` | `memory_context`, `memory_search` | Replace with CLI equivalents. 2 references. |\\n| **ai-council** | `.opencode/agents/ai-council.md:21,82,127` | `memory_context`, `memory_search`, `memory_match_triggers` | Replace with CLI equivalents. 3 references. |\\n| **deep-review** | `.opencode/agents/deep-review.md:250` | `memory_search`, `memory_context` | Replace with CLI equivalents. 2 references. |\\n| **debug** | `.opencode/agents/debug.md:136` | `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, `memory_search` | Replace with CLI equivalents. 3 references. |\\n| **review** | `.opencode/agents/review.md:64` | `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, `memory_search` | Replace with CLI equivalents. 3 references. |\\n\\n**Migration estimate:** ~20 total references across 6 agent files. Each is a search-and-replace of tool name -> CLI command. *Low effort, low risk.*\\n\\n#### Surface 2: Command Workflows (YAML assets)\\n\\nEvery command YAML that references MCP tools must switch to CLI invocations.\\n\\n**Evidence from grep across `.opencode/commands/`:**\\n\\n| Command | YAML Asset | MCP Tools Used | Migration Impact |\\n|---------|-----------|---------------|-----------------|\\n| `/speckit:resume` | `speckit_resume_auto.yaml`, `speckit_resume_confirm.yaml` | `memory_context`, `memory_search`, `session_bootstrap` | ~15 references total. Replace with `spec-memory context/search/bootstrap`. |\\n| `/speckit:plan` | `speckit_plan_auto.yaml`, `speckit_plan_confirm.yaml` | `memory_search` | ~8 references. |\\n| `/speckit:implement` | `speckit_implement_auto.yaml`, `speckit_implement_confirm.yaml` | `memory_search` | ~4 references. |\\n| `/speckit:complete` | `speckit_complete_auto.yaml`, `speckit_complete_confirm.yaml` | `memory_context`, `memory_search` | ~10 references. |\\n| `/deep:start-research-loop` | `deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml`, `deep_start-research-loop_confirm.yaml` | `memory_context`, `mk-spec-memory` (server name) | ~5 references. |\\n| `/deep:start-review-loop` | `deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml`, `deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml` | `memory_context`, `mk-spec-memory` (server name) | ~5 references. |\\n| `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` | `deep_start-agent-improvement-loop_auto.yaml`, `deep_start-agent-improvement-loop_confirm.yaml` | `memory_search` | ~2 references. |\\n| `/deep:ask-ai-council` | `deep_ask-ai-council_confirm.yaml` | `memory_context` | ~1 reference. |\\n| `/doctor` | `doctor_memory.yaml`, `doctor_mcp_debug.yaml`, `doctor_mcp_install.yaml`, `doctor_update.yaml`, `doctor_causal-graph.yaml`, `_routes.yaml` | `memory_search`, `memory_context`, `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` | ~30 references. The `/doctor` routes are the heaviest integration surface. `_routes.yaml:37-129` [SOURCE: file:.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:37] maps 9 route entries to `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search` and `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context`. |\\n\\n**Migration estimate:** ~80 total references across ~16 YAML assets. Each is a string replacement. *Medium effort, low risk.*\\n\\n#### Surface 3: Runtime Hooks\\n\\n**Evidence from codebase:** The `context-server.ts:52-64` imports hooks for `autoSurfaceMemories`, `primeSessionIfNeeded`, `appendAutoSurfaceHints`. These are injected automatically by the MCP server into tool responses. Under a CLI, these would NOT auto-fire unless:\\n1. The daemon is still running (architectures b/c), OR\\n2. The CLI explicitly calls `spec-memory bootstrap` first (architecture a).\\n\\n**Impact:** Under architecture (a), agents lose automatic \\\"session priming\\\" — the constitutional memory injection that happens on first tool call. Agents must explicitly `spec-memory bootstrap` at session start. Under architectures (b)/(c), the daemon provides the same auto-surface behavior through the IPC bridge, but the CLI client must request it explicitly (no automatic MCP response interceptor).\\n\\n**Migration estimate:** Add `spec-memory bootstrap` call to session startup instructions in AGENTS.md. *Low effort, medium behavioral impact.*\\n\\n#### Surface 4: OpenCode Configuration (opencode.json)\\n\\n**Current state:** The `opencode.json` MCP server config registers `mk-spec-memory` as a named MCP server:\\n```\\n\\\"mk-spec-memory\\\": {\\n  \\\"command\\\": \\\"node\\\",\\n  \\\"args\\\": [\\\".opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs\\\"]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Migration:** Replace with a shell tool registration. The CLI `spec-memory` needs to be discoverable as a registered tool. Under OpenCode, this means either:\\n- A new `tools` section for CLI-style tools (not just MCP servers), OR\\n- A shell-level alias that OpenCode's built-in shell execution can discover.\\n\\n**Impact:** This is an OpenCode runtime change, not a spec-kit change. It requires OpenCode to support \\\"registered shell tools\\\" with per-subcommand permission gating. This is the **highest-risk migration point** because it touches the runtime itself.\\n\\n#### Surface 5: Deep-Loop Allowed-Tools\\n\\n**Evidence:** `deep-start-research-loop_auto.yaml` and `deep-start-review-loop_auto.yaml` both list `mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]` [SOURCE: file:.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml:88] and use `memory_context` as the primary context tool.\\n\\n**Migration:** Under architecture (b)/(c), the deep-loop executor (fanout-run.cjs) would use `spawn('spec-memory', ['search', ...])` instead of MCP dispatch. The allowed-tools list changes from MCP tool names to CLI subcommand names.\\n\\n**Migration estimate:** ~10 references across 4 YAML files. *Low effort, low risk.*\\n\\n#### Surface 6: Constitutionals and Memory Index Scan\\n\\n**Evidence from `context-server.ts`:** The `initIngestJobQueue()`, `startFileWatcher()`, `findConstitutionalFiles()`, and `indexSingleFile()` functions are built into the daemon startup. Under architecture (a), the CLI would need to call these explicitly.\\n\\n**Impact:** Agents lose implicit file indexing. They must explicitly run `spec-memory index-scan` when they create new spec documents. This is a behavioral change for agent authors but not a feature loss — the functionality exists, it just needs explicit invocation.\\n\\n### Migration Effort Summary\\n\\n| Surface | Files Affected | Reference Count | Effort | Risk |\\n|---------|---------------|-----------------|--------|------|\\n| Agent allowed-tools | 6 .md files | ~20 | Low | Low |\\n| Command YAML assets | 16 .yaml files | ~80 | Medium | Low |\\n| Runtime hooks / session priming | context-server.ts, AGENTS.md | ~5 call sites | Low | Medium |\\n| OpenCode config (opencode.json) | opencode.json, runtime | ~1 config entry | **High** | **High** |\\n| Deep-loop allowed-tools | 4 .yaml files | ~10 | Low | Low |\\n| Constitutionals / index scan | context-server.ts | ~3 call sites | Low | Medium |\\n\\n**Total:** ~120 references across ~29 files.\\n\\n**Critical path:** The OpenCode runtime change (surface 4) is the only blocking dependency on an external team. Everything else is internal to the spec-kit repo.\\n\\n## Ruled Out\\n- (none)\\n\\n## Next Focus Shifts To\\nKQ5 — final architecture comparison with effort estimates, risk register, and go/no-go recommendation.\\n\",\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/iterations/iteration-004.md\"},\"output\":\"Wrote file successfully.\",\"metadata\":{\"diagnostics\":{},\"filepath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/iterations/iteration-004.md\",\"exists\":false,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/iterations/iteration-004.md\",\"time\":{\"start\":1780736285937,\"end\":1780736285956}},\"id\":\"prt_e9c26c4ba001i5706ecasBUkEk\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_163de1863ffeK7dtB9Aq2sZ9Js\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e9c26b874001XipL6CjthqoJRe\"}}\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/deepseek/iterations/iteration-004.md:| `/doctor` | `doctor_memory.yaml`, `doctor_mcp_debug.yaml`, `doctor_mcp_install.yaml`, `doctor_update.yaml`, `doctor_causal-graph.yaml`, `_routes.yaml` | `memory_search`, `memory_context`, `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` | ~30 references. The `/doctor` routes are the heaviest integration surface. `_routes.yaml:37-129` [SOURCE: file:.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:37] maps 9 route entries to `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search` and `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context`. |\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/001-hook-parity/005-fix-opencode-plugin-loader-bridge/spec.md:| REQ-009 | No regression in `opencode.json` MCP-server bootstrap                                             | After fix: `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` tools, `mcp__cocoindex_code__*` tools, and `mcp__code_mode__*` tools remain reachable from the TUI |\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/003-install-scripts-doctor-realignment/001-deep-research-install-scripts-doctor/research/findings-registry.json:      \"text\": \"**[P1 / STALE-LIVE]** `.opencode/commands/doctor/update.md:4` — `/doctor:update` frontmatter allows `mcp__mk_spec_memory__advisor_recommend/status/validate/rebuild`, but the workflow calls `mk_skill_advisor.advisor_rebuild({ force: true }) + mk_skill_advisor.advisor_validate({})` in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update.yaml:433`; live advisor rebuild/validation can be blocked by stale MCP tool ownership after advisor extraction.\",\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/003-install-scripts-doctor-realignment/001-deep-research-install-scripts-doctor/research/findings-registry.json:      \"text\": \"Important | SHARED-STALE | `.opencode/commands/doctor/update.md:4`, `.claude/commands/doctor/update.md:4` | Both `/doctor:update` frontmatter allow `mcp__mk_spec_memory__advisor_recommend`, `advisor_status`, `advisor_validate`, and `advisor_rebuild`; advisor ownership has moved to `mk_skill_advisor`, while the route manifest already uses `mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_*` at `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:112`.\",\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/003-install-scripts-doctor-realignment/001-deep-research-install-scripts-doctor/research/findings-registry.json:      \"text\": \"Clean after subtracting cataloged hits: `\\\\b11 (graph )?tools\\\\b`, `\\\\b39 tools\\\\b`, `\\\\b64 tools\\\\b`, `\\\\bccc\\\\b`, `coco.?daemon`, `\\\\b8765\\\\b`, `semantic search daemon`, `sk-research`, `sk-review`, `sk-agent-improvement`, and `mcp__mk_spec_memory__advisor`.\",\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/003-install-scripts-doctor-realignment/001-deep-research-install-scripts-doctor/research/deep-research-dashboard.md:- Clean after subtracting cataloged hits: `\\b11 (graph )?tools\\b`, `\\b39 tools\\b`, `\\b64 tools\\b`, `\\bccc\\b`, `coco.?daemon`, `\\b8765\\b`, `semantic search daemon`, `sk-research`, `sk-review`, `sk-agent-improvement`, and `mcp__mk_spec_memory__advisor`. (iteration 6)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/003-install-scripts-doctor-realignment/001-deep-research-install-scripts-doctor/research/deltas/iter-006.jsonl:{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"id\":\"r-iter006-004\",\"label\":\"mcp__mk_spec_memory__advisor had zero net-new hits after catalog subtraction\",\"iteration\":6}\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/003-install-scripts-doctor-realignment/001-deep-research-install-scripts-doctor/research/deltas/iter-005.jsonl:{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-iter005-004\",\"severity\":\"important\",\"classification\":\"SHARED-STALE\",\"summary\":\"Both /doctor:update frontmatters still allow advisor tools under mk-spec-memory.\",\"evidence\":[\".opencode/commands/doctor/update.md:4 includes mcp__mk_spec_memory__advisor_recommend/advisor_status/advisor_validate/advisor_rebuild\",\".claude/commands/doctor/update.md:4 includes mcp__mk_spec_memory__advisor_recommend/advisor_status/advisor_validate/advisor_rebuild\",\".opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:112 - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend\"],\"current_truth\":\"advisor_recommend/status/validate/rebuild belong to mk_skill_advisor.\"}\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/003-install-scripts-doctor-realignment/001-deep-research-install-scripts-doctor/research/research.md:| **advisor MCP tools** | `mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_*` | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__advisor_*` (`doctor/update.md:4`) |\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/003-install-scripts-doctor-realignment/001-deep-research-install-scripts-doctor/research/research.md:| C-12 | P1 | `doctor/update.md:4` | frontmatter `mcp__mk_spec_memory__advisor_{recommend,status,validate,rebuild}` → `mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_*` |\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/006-operator-tooling/003-install-scripts-doctor-realignment/001-deep-research-install-scripts-doctor/research/prompts/iteration-6.md:    - Advisor ownership: `mcp__mk_spec_memory__advisor`.\n===\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:allowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context({\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:| Context (preferred) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context({ input, ... })` | SINGLE | Fall back to manual search |\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:| Quick search (optional) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search({ query, ... })` | SINGLE | Fall back to preferred/manual retrieval |\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:| Trigger check | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers({ prompt: query })` | OPTIONAL | Continue without |\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:| Search (manual) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search({ query, anchors, includeContent: true })` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:> **Note:** The dedicated `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context()` tool provides unified intent-aware retrieval server-side. It accepts `input`, `mode`, `intent`, `specFolder`, governed retrieval params (`tenantId`, `userId`, `agentId`), `limit`, `sessionId`, `enableDedup`, `includeContent`, `includeTrace`, `tokenUsage`, and `anchors`. `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search()` also supports governed retrieval via `tenantId`, `userId`, and `agentId`. This is the recommended unified approach. The manual orchestration below is for advanced use cases requiring fine-grained control.\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context({\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search({\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search({\n===\n","exit":0,"description":"Find mcp__mk_spec_memory invocations across agents/commands/hooks","truncated":false},"title":"Find mcp__mk_spec_memory invocations across agents/commands/hooks","time":{"start":1780737101828,"end":1780737101830}},"id":"prt_e9c33a963001160yFksYbSqJZh","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","messageID":"msg_e9c3377b8001RjBTVpKuEiKTBw"}}
