{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780737363382,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_function_yq1ik283jkqq_1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/deep-research-strategy.md","oldString":"## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n- KQ1 — 37-tool parity matrix: 5 tools already ported (generate-context, cli.ts stats/bulk-delete, reindex-embeddings, validate-memory-quality); 32 are 1:1 handler ports with a CLI argv layer. 0 truly lost in the handler sense.\n- KQ2 — daemon-dependency audit: 6 services catalogued (S1..S6); 24/37 tools are daemon-free, 13/37 are soft-dependent, 0 are hard-required. Per-architecture loss table: (a) loses 3 services (S1, S2, S4); (b) keeps all 6; (c) keeps all 6 + auto-spawn.\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n\n## 6. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Reading `TOOL_NAMES` sets as the source of truth is fast and produces a verifiable 37-row matrix (iteration 1).\n- Tracing `startFileWatcher` and its only call site in `dist/context-server.js:1740` is the cleanest way to determine daemon-only services (iteration 2).\n- Reading `spec-folder-mutex.ts:14-86` and `working-memory.ts:171-623` to verify \"interprocess\" / \"per-session\" claims (iteration 2).\n\n## 7. WHAT FAILED\n\n- (none this iteration)\n\n## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n- (none yet)\n\n## 9. RULED-OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- \"11 CLIs\" framing as broad parity evidence (iteration 1, finding 1.9).\n- Treating KQ1 parity matrix as a sufficient zero-loss verdict (iteration 1, finding 1.8).\n- \"Single-writer = daemon-resident\" claim — interprocess by design (iteration 2, ruled-out block).\n- \"Warm session briefs = daemon hot-cache\" claim — per-session SQLite rows, not in-memory daemon cache (iteration 2, finding 2.8).\n\n## 10. NEXT FOCUS\n\nKQ3 — MCP-only affordances and concrete CLI replacements. Three \"LOST\" rows in the per-architecture loss table need replacement designs: tool-schema auto-discovery, per-tool runtime permissioning, `-32001` retryable semantics. The session-proxy replay classification is already covered (kept in b/c; CLI implements its own retry in a).","newString":"## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n- KQ1 — 37-tool parity matrix: 5 tools already ported (generate-context, cli.ts stats/bulk-delete, reindex-embeddings, validate-memory-quality); 32 are 1:1 handler ports with a CLI argv layer. 0 truly lost in the handler sense.\n- KQ2 — daemon-dependency audit: 6 services catalogued (S1..S6); 24/37 tools are daemon-free, 13/37 are soft-dependent, 0 are hard-required. Per-architecture loss table: (a) loses 3 services (S1, S2, S4); (b) keeps all 6; (c) keeps all 6 + auto-spawn.\n- KQ3 — MCP-only affordances: 5 affordances catalogued (A1..A5); only A5 (auto-surface hooks) is architecture-dependent and **lost** in (a); A1, A2, A3, A4 are all replaced (never \"lost\") via per-runtime surfaces. 4x5 cross-runtime migration matrix built.\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n\n## 6. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Reading `TOOL_NAMES` sets as the source of truth is fast and produces a verifiable 37-row matrix (iteration 1).\n- Tracing `startFileWatcher` and its only call site in `dist/context-server.js:1740` is the cleanest way to determine daemon-only services (iteration 2).\n- Reading `spec-folder-mutex.ts:14-86` and `working-memory.ts:171-623` to verify \"interprocess\" / \"per-session\" claims (iteration 2).\n- Mapping each MCP affordance to a 4-runtime replacement matrix (iteration 3) — surfaces that A1 is per-runtime, not uniform.\n\n## 7. WHAT FAILED\n\n- (none this iteration)\n\n## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n- (none yet)\n\n## 9. RULED-OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- \"11 CLIs\" framing as broad parity evidence (iteration 1, finding 1.9).\n- Treating KQ1 parity matrix as a sufficient zero-loss verdict (iteration 1, finding 1.8).\n- \"Single-writer = daemon-resident\" claim — interprocess by design (iteration 2, ruled-out block).\n- \"Warm session briefs = daemon hot-cache\" claim — per-session SQLite rows, not in-memory daemon cache (iteration 2, finding 2.8).\n- A1 tool-schema auto-discovery as a uniform problem — per-runtime, OpenCode is the only case needing runtime support (iteration 3, finding 3.7 + 3.8).\n- A5 auto-surface as a single replacement problem — architecture-dependent (iteration 3, finding 3.6).\n\n## 10. NEXT FOCUS\n\nKQ4 — integration-surface migration. Enumerate the actual files (agents + commands + doctor routes + AGENTS.md) that need to be edited, count the references, and produce the per-surface effort estimate. KQ4 output feeds KQ5's risk register directly."},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -30,16 +30,18 @@\n ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n \n - KQ1 — 37-tool parity matrix: 5 tools already ported (generate-context, cli.ts stats/bulk-delete, reindex-embeddings, validate-memory-quality); 32 are 1:1 handler ports with a CLI argv layer. 0 truly lost in the handler sense.\n - KQ2 — daemon-dependency audit: 6 services catalogued (S1..S6); 24/37 tools are daemon-free, 13/37 are soft-dependent, 0 are hard-required. Per-architecture loss table: (a) loses 3 services (S1, S2, S4); (b) keeps all 6; (c) keeps all 6 + auto-spawn.\n+- KQ3 — MCP-only affordances: 5 affordances catalogued (A1..A5); only A5 (auto-surface hooks) is architecture-dependent and **lost** in (a); A1, A2, A3, A4 are all replaced (never \"lost\") via per-runtime surfaces. 4x5 cross-runtime migration matrix built.\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n \n ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n \n - Reading `TOOL_NAMES` sets as the source of truth is fast and produces a verifiable 37-row matrix (iteration 1).\n - Tracing `startFileWatcher` and its only call site in `dist/context-server.js:1740` is the cleanest way to determine daemon-only services (iteration 2).\n - Reading `spec-folder-mutex.ts:14-86` and `working-memory.ts:171-623` to verify \"interprocess\" / \"per-session\" claims (iteration 2).\n+- Mapping each MCP affordance to a 4-runtime replacement matrix (iteration 3) — surfaces that A1 is per-runtime, not uniform.\n \n ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n \n - (none this iteration)\n@@ -53,12 +55,14 @@\n - \"11 CLIs\" framing as broad parity evidence (iteration 1, finding 1.9).\n - Treating KQ1 parity matrix as a sufficient zero-loss verdict (iteration 1, finding 1.8).\n - \"Single-writer = daemon-resident\" claim — interprocess by design (iteration 2, ruled-out block).\n - \"Warm session briefs = daemon hot-cache\" claim — per-session SQLite rows, not in-memory daemon cache (iteration 2, finding 2.8).\n+- A1 tool-schema auto-discovery as a uniform problem — per-runtime, OpenCode is the only case needing runtime support (iteration 3, finding 3.7 + 3.8).\n+- A5 auto-surface as a single replacement problem — architecture-dependent (iteration 3, finding 3.6).\n \n ## 10. NEXT FOCUS\n \n-KQ3 — MCP-only affordances and concrete CLI replacements. Three \"LOST\" rows in the per-architecture loss table need replacement designs: tool-schema auto-discovery, per-tool runtime permissioning, `-32001` retryable semantics. The session-proxy replay classification is already covered (kept in b/c; CLI implements its own retry in a).\n+KQ4 — integration-surface migration. Enumerate the actual files (agents + commands + doctor routes + AGENTS.md) that need to be edited, count the references, and produce the per-surface effort estimate. KQ4 output feeds KQ5's risk register directly.\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 11. KNOWN CONTEXT (analyst-owned)\n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/deep-research-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -30,16 +30,18 @@\n ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n \n - KQ1 — 37-tool parity matrix: 5 tools already ported (generate-context, cli.ts stats/bulk-delete, reindex-embeddings, validate-memory-quality); 32 are 1:1 handler ports with a CLI argv layer. 0 truly lost in the handler sense.\n - KQ2 — daemon-dependency audit: 6 services catalogued (S1..S6); 24/37 tools are daemon-free, 13/37 are soft-dependent, 0 are hard-required. Per-architecture loss table: (a) loses 3 services (S1, S2, S4); (b) keeps all 6; (c) keeps all 6 + auto-spawn.\n+- KQ3 — MCP-only affordances: 5 affordances catalogued (A1..A5); only A5 (auto-surface hooks) is architecture-dependent and **lost** in (a); A1, A2, A3, A4 are all replaced (never \"lost\") via per-runtime surfaces. 4x5 cross-runtime migration matrix built.\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n \n ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n \n - Reading `TOOL_NAMES` sets as the source of truth is fast and produces a verifiable 37-row matrix (iteration 1).\n - Tracing `startFileWatcher` and its only call site in `dist/context-server.js:1740` is the cleanest way to determine daemon-only services (iteration 2).\n - Reading `spec-folder-mutex.ts:14-86` and `working-memory.ts:171-623` to verify \"interprocess\" / \"per-session\" claims (iteration 2).\n+- Mapping each MCP affordance to a 4-runtime replacement matrix (iteration 3) — surfaces that A1 is per-runtime, not uniform.\n \n ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n \n - (none this iteration)\n@@ -53,12 +55,14 @@\n - \"11 CLIs\" framing as broad parity evidence (iteration 1, finding 1.9).\n - Treating KQ1 parity matrix as a sufficient zero-loss verdict (iteration 1, finding 1.8).\n - \"Single-writer = daemon-resident\" claim — interprocess by design (iteration 2, ruled-out block).\n - \"Warm session briefs = daemon hot-cache\" claim — per-session SQLite rows, not in-memory daemon cache (iteration 2, finding 2.8).\n+- A1 tool-schema auto-discovery as a uniform problem — per-runtime, OpenCode is the only case needing runtime support (iteration 3, finding 3.7 + 3.8).\n+- A5 auto-surface as a single replacement problem — architecture-dependent (iteration 3, finding 3.6).\n \n ## 10. NEXT FOCUS\n \n-KQ3 — MCP-only affordances and concrete CLI replacements. Three \"LOST\" rows in the per-architecture loss table need replacement designs: tool-schema auto-discovery, per-tool runtime permissioning, `-32001` retryable semantics. The session-proxy replay classification is already covered (kept in b/c; CLI implements its own retry in a).\n+KQ4 — integration-surface migration. Enumerate the actual files (agents + commands + doctor routes + AGENTS.md) that need to be edited, count the references, and produce the per-surface effort estimate. KQ4 output feeds KQ5's risk register directly.\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 11. KNOWN CONTEXT (analyst-owned)\n","additions":5,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1780737363375,"end":1780737363379}},"id":"prt_e9c377f0c001jBvivO3jxkrOtT","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","messageID":"msg_e9c3758740010DRKtPlBwGh7lQ"}}
