y\": \"P0\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f-iter002-002\", \"label\": \"Architecture (a) loses 3 services (S1 warm embedder, S2 file-watcher, S4 RSS watchdog); (b) and (c) keep all 6\", \"iteration\": 2, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f-iter002-003\", \"label\": \"The single-writer lease (S5) is interprocess (mkdir-based) by design — all 3 architectures inherit it for free\", \"iteration\": 2, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f-iter002-004\", \"label\": \"Architecture (c) is the strict superset of (b) in feature retention and the strict superset of (a) in robustness — only cost is a one-time 2-3s cold start on the very first call\", \"iteration\": 2, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-001\", \"label\": \"5 MCP-only affordances catalogued (A1..A5); only A5 (auto-surface hooks) is architecture-dependent and lost in (a); A1, A2, A3, A4 are all replaced via per-runtime surfaces (never truly lost)\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-002\", \"label\": \"OpenCode 'tools:' block is the only blocking external runtime dependency; Claude/Codex/Copilot use existing permission surfaces (Bash allow-list, --approval-policy, permissions-matrix.json)\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-003\", \"label\": \"Zod boundary validation is transport-agnostic; the CLI re-uses the same module (schemas/tool-input-schemas.ts:30) and the cost is one line per subcommand\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-004\", \"label\": \"Session-proxy replay (-32001 retryable vs -32002 protocol mismatch) is preserved unchanged in (b)/(c); (a) implements its own ENOTCONN retry with identical user-visible cost\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P1\"}\n  ],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n    {\"direction\": \"11 CLIs framing as broad parity evidence\", \"reason\": \"10/11 are operational utilities, not user-facing tool substitutes\", \"iteration\": 1},\n    {\"direction\": \"Treat KQ1 matrix as 