{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780737501492,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_function_2rpp37yw0xka_1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"grep \"mk-spec-memory\\|mcp__mk_spec_memory\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/manage.md | head -20\necho \"===\"\nls /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/\necho \"===\"\ngrep \"mcp__mk_spec_memory\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md | sort -u | head -20","description":"Look at manage.md and search.md references"},"output":"allowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_restore, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({ force: true })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({ force: false })  // Normal incremental\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({ force: true })   // Force full re-index\n2. Execute `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep({ dryRun: true })` for previews.\n4. Execute `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep({ dryRun: false })` only after confirmation.\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete({\n3. **Execute:** `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update({ id: <id>, importanceTier: \"<tier>\" })`\n2. Execute: `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate({ id: <id>, wasUseful: <bool> })`\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list({ limit: 100, sortBy: \"created_at\" })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete({ id: <id> })\nExecute `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health({})`. Display:\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create({\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list({ limit: 50, specFolder: \"<folder>\" })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete({ name: \"<checkpoint_name>\", confirmName: \"<checkpoint_name>\" })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start({\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status({ jobId: \"<jobId>\" })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel({ jobId: \"<jobId>\" })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats({})\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list({ limit: N, sortBy: \"created_at\", specFolder: \"optional\" })\n===\nREADME.txt\nlearn.md\nmanage.md\nsave.md\nsearch.md\n===\n> **Note:** The dedicated `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context()` tool provides unified intent-aware retrieval server-side. It accepts `input`, `mode`, `intent`, `specFolder`, governed retrieval params (`tenantId`, `userId`, `agentId`), `limit`, `sessionId`, `enableDedup`, `includeContent`, `includeTrace`, `tokenUsage`, and `anchors`. `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search()` also supports governed retrieval via `tenantId`, `userId`, and `agentId`. This is the recommended unified approach. The manual orchestration below is for advanced use cases requiring fine-grained control.\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard({ sprintFilter, channelFilter, metricFilter, limit, format })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation({ mode: \"ablation\", channels, groundTruthQueryIds, recallK, storeResults: true, includeFormattedReport: true })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link({ sourceId, targetId, relation, strength, evidence })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats({})\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink({ edgeId })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context({\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why({ memoryId, maxDepth, direction, relations, includeMemoryDetails })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history({ specFolder, sessionId, limit, onlyComplete, includeSummary })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search({\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search({\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight({ specFolder, taskId, knowledgeScore, uncertaintyScore, contextScore, gapsClosed, newGapsDiscovered })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight({ specFolder, taskId, knowledgeScore, uncertaintyScore, contextScore, knowledgeGaps, sessionId })\n| Context (preferred) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context({ input, ... })` | SINGLE | Fall back to manual search |\n| Quick search (optional) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search({ query, ... })` | SINGLE | Fall back to preferred/manual retrieval |\n| Search (manual) | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search({ query, anchors, includeContent: true })` | SINGLE | Show error msg |\n| Trigger check | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers({ prompt: query })` | OPTIONAL | Continue without |\n","metadata":{"output":"allowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_restore, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({ force: true })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({ force: false })  // Normal incremental\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan({ force: true })   // Force full re-index\n2. Execute `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep({ dryRun: true })` for previews.\n4. Execute `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep({ dryRun: false })` only after confirmation.\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete({\n3. **Execute:** `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update({ id: <id>, importanceTier: \"<tier>\" })`\n2. Execute: `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate({ id: <id>, wasUseful: <bool> })`\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list({ limit: 100, sortBy: \"created_at\" })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete({ id: <id> })\nExecute `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health({})`. Display:\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create({\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list({ limit: 50, specFolder: \"<folder>\" })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete({ name: \"<checkpoint_name>\", confirmName: \"<checkpoint_name>\" })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start({\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status({ jobId: \"<jobId>\" })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel({ jobId: \"<jobId>\" })\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats({})\nmcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list({ limit: N, sortBy: \"created_at\", specFolder: \"optional\" })\n===\nREADME.txt\nlearn.md\nmanage.md\nsave.md\nsearch.md\n===\n> **Note:** The dedicated `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context()` tool provides unified intent-aware retrieval server-side. It accepts `input`, `mode`, `intent`, `specFolder`, governed retrieval params (`tenantId`, `userId`, `agentId`), `limit`, `sessionId`, `enableDedup`, `includeContent`, `includeT