{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780737513936,"sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_function_pqtu0nau74jx_1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/\necho \"===\"\ngrep \"mk-spec-memory\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/mcp-doctor.sh | head -10\necho \"===\"\ngrep \"mk-spec-memory\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md | head -10\necho \"===\"\ngrep \"mk-spec-memory\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md | head -10\necho \"===\"\ngrep \"mk-spec-memory\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/update.md | head -10","description":"Check doctor scripts and update.md"},"output":"audit_descriptions.py\ndoctor-runtime-bootstrap.sh\nmcp-doctor-lib.sh\nmcp-doctor.sh\nroute-validate.py\nroute-validate.sh\n===\n#                       Names: mk-spec-memory, mk_skill_advisor, mk_code_index, code_mode, sequential_thinking\n                      Names: mk-spec-memory, mk_skill_advisor, mk_code_index, code_mode, sequential_thinking\n  mk-spec-memory       Spec Kit Memory (Node.js MCP, SQLite + embeddings)\n  local srv=\"mk-spec-memory\"\n  local -a servers=(\"mk-spec-memory\" \"mk_skill_advisor\" \"mk_code_index\" \"code_mode\" \"sequential_thinking\")\nshould_run \"mk-spec-memory\"      && diagnose_mk_spec_memory\n===\n> Examples: `/doctor:mcp install --server mk-spec-memory`, `/doctor:mcp debug --fix`\n/doctor:mcp install --server mk-spec-memory         # Install just mk-spec-memory\n===\n===\n- **MCP STARTUP BOOTSTRAP**: `mk-spec-memory` config points to `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`, not directly to `dist/context-server.js`. The launcher may build missing TypeScript output before OpenCode registers MCP tools.\nWhen `STATUS=RESTART_REQUIRED`, no database rebuild has started yet. Start a fresh OpenCode process so the MCP launcher can register the now-built `mk-spec-memory` surface, then rerun `/doctor:update --resume-bootstrap`.\n","metadata":{"output":"audit_descriptions.py\ndoctor-runtime-bootstrap.sh\nmcp-doctor-lib.sh\nmcp-doctor.sh\nroute-validate.py\nroute-validate.sh\n===\n#                       Names: mk-spec-memory, mk_skill_advisor, mk_code_index, code_mode, sequential_thinking\n                      Names: mk-spec-memory, mk_skill_advisor, mk_code_index, code_mode, sequential_thinking\n  mk-spec-memory       Spec Kit Memory (Node.js MCP, SQLite + embeddings)\n  local srv=\"mk-spec-memory\"\n  local -a servers=(\"mk-spec-memory\" \"mk_skill_advisor\" \"mk_code_index\" \"code_mode\" \"sequential_thinking\")\nshould_run \"mk-spec-memory\"      && diagnose_mk_spec_memory\n===\n> Examples: `/doctor:mcp install --server mk-spec-memory`, `/doctor:mcp debug --fix`\n/doctor:mcp install --server mk-spec-memory         # Install just mk-spec-memory\n===\n===\n- **MCP STARTUP BOOTSTRAP**: `mk-spec-memory` config points to `.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs`, not directly to `dist/context-server.js`. The launcher may build missing TypeScript output before OpenCode registers MCP tools.\nWhen `STATUS=RESTART_REQUIRED`, no database rebuild has started yet. Start a fresh OpenCode process so the MCP launcher can register the now-built `mk-spec-memory` surface, then rerun `/doctor:update --resume-bootstrap`.\n","exit":0,"description":"Check doctor scripts and update.md","truncated":false},"title":"Check doctor scripts and update.md","time":{"start":1780737513933,"end":1780737513935}},"id":"prt_e9c3a0b14001mBC3PrOr7wvzSe","sessionID":"ses_163de1863ffeLd3K58IkmWaFwL","messageID":"msg_e9c39eb1d0012WH07Nu6a55648"}}
