tion\": \"S2 as 'just search-and-replace'\", \"reason\": \"Inline tool calls in prompt bodies require CLI flag-syntax rewrite; cost is ~2x a pure search-and-replace\", \"iteration\": 4},\n-    {\"direction\": \"S3 as 'just config edit'\", \"reason\": \"OpenCode 'tools:' block is an external runtime dependency; S3 is the migration critical path\", \"iteration\": 4}\n+    {\"direction\": \"S2 as 'just search-and-replace'\", \"reason\": \"Inline tool calls in prompt bodies require CLI flag-syntax rewrite\", \"iteration\": 4},\n+    {\"direction\": \"S3 as 'just config edit'\", \"reason\": \"OpenCode 'tools:' block is the migration critical path\", \"iteration\": 4},\n+    {\"direction\": \"Single-binary CLI form\", \"reason\": \"Multi-process by design; CLI is one entry point, not one process\", \"iteration\": 5},\n+    {\"direction\": \"Atomic migration\", \"reason\": \"Composable per-tool and per-runtime; only S3 is truly atomic\", \"iteration\": 5},\n+    {\"direction\": \"(a) as the recommended architecture\", \"reason\": \"Operational cost (R1, R3, R5, R6) exceeds migration saving\", \"iteration\": 5}\n   ]\n }\n \n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/findings-registry.json","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages/minimax/findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,39 +1,44 @@\n {\n-  \"openQuestions\": [\n-    {\"id\": \"kq5\", \"label\": \"KQ5 — Architecture a/b/c comparison with go/no-go (final synthesis)\"}\n-  ],\n+  \"openQuestions\": [],\n   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n     {\"id\": \"kq1\", \"label\": \"KQ1 — 37-tool parity matrix\", \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-001.md finding 1.1; 5 already ported, 32 port-able, 0 truly lost in handler sense\"},\n     {\"id\": \"kq2\", \"label\": \"KQ2 — Daemon-dependency audit\", \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-002.md findings 2.1-2.3; 6 services S1..S6 catalogued, 24/37 daemon-free, 13/37 soft, 0 hard; per-arch loss table built\"},\n     {\"id\": \"kq3\", \"label\": \"KQ3 — MCP-only affordances and concrete CLI replacements\", \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-003.md findings 3.1-3.7; 5 affordances A1..A5 catalogued; only A5 is lost in (a); 4x5 cross-runtime replacement matrix built\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"kq4\", \"label\": \"KQ4 — Integration-surface migration\", \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-004.md findings 4.1-4.7; 5 surfaces S1..S5; 28 files / ~125 refs; S1+S2+S4+S5 = 1-3 days mechanical; S3 (OpenCode tools: block) = 1-3 weeks gate\"}\n+    {\"id\": \"kq4\", \"label\": \"KQ4 — Integration-surface migration\", \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-004.md findings 4.1-4.7; 5 surfaces S1..S5; 28 files / ~125 refs; S1+S2+S4+S5 = 1-3 days mechanical; S3 (OpenCode tools: block) = 1-3 weeks gate\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"kq5\", \"label\": \"KQ5 — Architecture comparison + go/no-go\", \"evidence\": \"iterations/iteration-005.md findings 5.1-5.5; 5-dim scoring (a)=0.45, (b)=0.92, (c)=0.97; risk register 9 risks; **verdict: GO with architecture (c) — hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand**\"}\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\"id\": \"f-iter001-001\", \"label\": \"100% of the 37 MCP tools can be CLI-replaced in handler terms; 5 already ported today (generate-context, cli.ts stats/bulk-delete, reindex-embeddings, validate-memory-quality)\", \"iteration\": 1, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n     {\"id\": \"f-iter001-002\", \"label\": \"The handler layer is the parity surface, not the tool — the CLI just needs to reproduce parseArgs → validateToolArgs → handler → JSON.stringify(content)\", \"iteration\": 1, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"f-iter001-003\", \"label\": \"memory_quick_search is just memory_search with defaults (autoDetectIntent, enableDedup, includeContent, includeConstitutional, rerank all true) — no new handler\", \"iteration\": 1, \"severity\": \"P2\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"f-iter001-004\", \"label\": \"Causal and checkpoint tools (8 total) have no daemon requirement; they read/write SQLite + causal-edge/checkpoint tables directly\", \"iteration\": 1, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter001-003\", \"label\": \"memory_quick_search is just memory_search with defaults — no new handler\", \"iteration\": 1, \"severity\": \"P2\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter001-004\", \"label\": \"Causal and checkpoint tools (8 total) have no daemon requirement\", \"iteration\": 1, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n     {\"id\": \"f-iter002-001\", \"label\": \"6 daemon-resident services (S1..S6) catalogued; 24/37 tools are daemon-free, 13/37 are soft-dependent, 0 are hard-required\", \"iteration\": 2, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n     {\"id\": \"f-iter002-002\", \"label\": \"Architecture (a) loses 3 services (S1 warm embedder, S2 file-watcher, S4 RSS watchdog); (b) and (c) keep all 6\", \"iteration\": 2, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"f-iter002-003\", \"label\": \"The single-writer lease (S5) is interprocess (mkdir-based) by design — all 3 architectures inherit it for free\", \"iteration\": 2, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"f-iter002-004\", \"label\": \"Architecture (c) is the strict superset of (b) in feature retention and the strict superset of (a) in robustness — only cost is a one-time 2-3s cold start on the very first call\", \"iteration\": 2, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-001\", \"label\": \"5 MCP-only affordances catalogued (A1..A5); only A5 (auto-surface hooks) is architecture-dependent and lost in (a); A1, A2, A3, A4 are all replaced via per-runtime surfaces (never truly lost)\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-002\", \"label\": \"OpenCode 'tools:' block is the only blocking external runtime dependency; Claude/Codex/Copilot use existing permission surfaces (Bash allow-list, --approval-policy, permissions-matrix.json)\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-003\", \"label\": \"Zod boundary validation is transport-agnostic; the CLI re-uses the same module (schemas/tool-input-schemas.ts:30) and the cost is one line per subcommand\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-004\", \"label\": \"Session-proxy replay (-32001 retryable vs -32002 protocol mismatch) is preserved unchanged in (b)/(c); (a) implements its own ENOTCONN retry with identical user-visible cost\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"f-iter004-001\", \"label\": \"5 migration surfaces catalogued (S1..S5): 6 agent files, 19 command files, 1 root opencode.json, AGENTS.md, doctor scripts. 28 files / ~125 references total\", \"iteration\": 4, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"f-iter004-002\", \"label\": \"S1+S2+S4+S5 migration is mechanical: 1-3 days of search-and-replace. S2 has 106 refs across 19 files; 34 of those are inline tool calls requiring CLI flag-syntax rewrite (manage.md is heaviest)\", \"iteration\": 4, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n-    {\"id\": \"f-iter004-003\", \"label\": \"S3 (OpenCode 'tools:' block) is the only external runtime dependency; either OpenCode ships it (1-3 weeks) or we ship a CLI diagnostic shim (2-3 days). S3 is the migration critical path.\", \"iteration\": 4, \"severity\": \"P0\"}\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter002-003\", \"label\": \"The single-writer lease (S5) is interprocess by design — all 3 architectures inherit it for free\", \"iteration\": 2, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter002-004\", \"label\": \"Architecture (c) is the strict superset of (b) in feature retention and the strict superset of (a) in robustness\", \"iteration\": 2, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-001\", \"label\": \"5 MCP-only affordances catalogued; only A5 is lost in (a); A1..A4 all replaced via per-runtime surfaces\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-002\", \"label\": \"OpenCode 'tools:' block is the only blocking external runtime dependency; Claude/Codex/Copilot use existing permission surfaces\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-003\", \"label\": \"Zod boundary validation is transport-agnostic; cost is one line per subcommand\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter003-004\", \"label\": \"Session-proxy replay (-32001/-32002) is preserved unchanged in (b)/(c); (a) implements its own ENOTCONN retry\", \"iteration\": 3, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter004-001\", \"label\": \"5 migration surfaces catalogued; 28 files / ~125 references total\", \"iteration\": 4, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter004-002\", \"label\": \"S1+S2+S4+S5 migration is mechanical: 1-3 days; S2 has 34 inline calls in manage.md requiring CLI flag-syntax rewrite\", \"iteration\": 4, \"severity\": \"P1\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter004-003\", \"label\": \"S3 (OpenCode 'tools:' block) is the migration critical path: 1-3 weeks if OpenCode ships, 2-3 days for CLI shim\", \"iteration\": 4, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter005-001\", \"label\": \"5-dimension scoring: (a)=0.45, (b)=0.92, (c)=0.97. Architecture (c) is the unique strict-superset point in the 3-D Pareto space (feature retention × robustness × migration cost)\", \"iteration\": 5, \"severity\": \"P0\"},\n+    {\"id\": \"f-iter005-002\", \"label\": \"Risk register: (a) accumulates 1 HIGH + 4 MEDIUM risks; (b) and (c) accumulate 0 HIGH + 1 MEDIUM each\", \"iteration\": 5, \"severity\": \"P